I feel like I play Rosalina in a very unorthodox way.

I throw out aggressive options and go for deep reads, and also go for deep risky edge guards all the time.

I cover these risky options with safer gameplay when I need to, and a very high consistency with combos and strings.

I'm the Rosalina player that will spike Marth, Lucina, Corrin & K. Rool's recoveries.

I'll also camp with a lead or play ultra safe when I'm at high % and just don't want to lose.

I could probably be more successful if I just camped all the time, but its not my style. 😂
